# WitsV3 — Global Architecture

## Worktrees & docs

- Work from **`WitsV3-cursor`** (branch `cursor/work` or `cursor/*`). Personal runtime = sibling `WitsV3`; Claude = `WitsV3-claude` — see `WORKTREES.md`
- **Always read** `planning/roadmap/suggested-features-2026-07.md` for priorities and `README.md` for how it runs today
- Architecture ref: `planning/architecture/system-architecture.md` (many sections mid-2025 — trust README/roadmap for status)
- Shipped log: `planning/roadmap/revival-2026-07.md`
- Root `TASK.md` / `PLANNING.md` are **redirects only** — do not append phase checklists; update the suggested-features roadmap
- Legacy root `.cursorrules` is a one-line redirect here; canonical rules live under `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`

## Stack declaration

- **Python 3.10+**, **FastAPI + SSE** (`web/`), **Pydantic** (`core/schemas.py`), **Ollama** primary LLM
- Local-first orchestration: Web UI (primary) + CLI, ReAct orchestrator, tool registry, persistent memory, optional neural web / MCP

## Packages

- `agents/` — BaseAgent, orchestrators, control center, specialists
- `core/` — config, LLM, memory, schemas, safe_code_editor
- `tools/` — BaseTool implementations (auto-discovered)
- `web/` — FastAPI + SSE UI

## Task & docs standards

- Track new work in `planning/roadmap/suggested-features-2026-07.md`
- Log large shipped chunks in `planning/roadmap/revival-2026-07.md` when relevant
- Update `README.md` when install or user-facing behavior changes
- Prefer the canonical roadmap over proliferating “status” docs

## Critical

- Preserve the ReAct loop in orchestrators
- Maintain compatibility with existing tools/agents unless intentionally retiring them
- Prefer Ollama running for integration checks

## Don't Do

- Circular imports between packages
- Schema changes without updating dependents
